column11: HIGH IN COMPARISON TO LAST YEAR
HIGHER THAN LAST REPORT-NOW AT NORMAL DEPTH

column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Sunny- moderate wind- five boats on lake fishing.  One of two people on our lake take down the beaver dam on rice creek outlet- within four days the lake dropped 7"- what can we do
Clear skies- slight ripple on the water- and weed growth appears to be exceptionally profuse compared to last year.  Water level: up about 1"
Very humid and hot- high winds and rough water for the past two days and today.
After a cloudy cool day- skies became cloudless about 1: 30 and warmed up slightly.  Little boat activity.  Maples spotted along lakeshore in full bust of orange and red.
25 Ft out from shore algae level is so intense you cannot see bottom- appears to be a pea soup.  Winds were strong blowing from south on to west shore.
Overcast day with a strong south wind.  The water color is bluish green.

Someone on lake tears out beaver dam at outlet which lowers lake level to point where west shore is extremely low.  One resort on lake claims septic does not work when water level is high- someone needs to check out resort septic.
Need help establishing lake level!  temperature is the 60s- very sunny- clear skies- birch and aspen bright yellow- and dense algae 15 feet out from shore.
This is my last report until May 1993.
First report of 1993- pollen on shoreline water surface
Partly cloudy- lots of algae (green) loose along shore lines
Pair of loons nested on lake- now with a pair of babies
Sunny- clear skies- water is calm- best day so far for using disk.
Partly cloudy- wind from the north.
Slight surface scum of algae- clear skies- calm waters.
Slight whitish surface scum close to shore- some scattered sections of cut up surface weeds (have had a big boat racing around in bay where weeds are close to surface.  Day was sunny and calm.
Partly sunny sky- slight west wind- temp is 60 degrees.  No algae bloom- big rain storm last night.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- partly cloudy- choppy water- small plant particles in sample site.
Calm- sunny- loads of small particles suspended in water at the test site.
Sunny- clear skies- slight wave movement- intense fall color around the lake.
Cloudy- day after high wind storm- first report for 1994.
Pair of loons residents of lake with one chick- sunny-slight wind.
Clear skies- windy- only one boat on lake.
Clear and sunny- west wind- moderate surface movement- 4 boats on the lake
Sunny- clear skies- calm water.  Water level very- very low.
Clear skies- slight ripple on water.
Overcast- drizzle.  Lake level: very high
Pair of loons sighted on 6/12-very hot day-some evidence of algal scum on water.
Cloudy and some surface wave action.
Clear skies- wind from north-water level very low-pair of loons with two chicks.  Water level: very low.
Sunny-mid 80's-no boats on lake-past week had two big boats racing around.  Water level: Rising slowly from a very low level
Water has a greenish tint.  Partly sunny-moderate surface water movement.
Clear and sunny- moderate winds- moderate surface action of waters.
Slight greenish tint.  Clear + sunny-calm waters.  Pickerel weed in full bloom.
Gulls- osprey- eagles- loons on lake.  Clear skies-slight ripple to water.
Clear- 49 degrees- slight water ripple- suspended particles of algae floating on the surface.  Lake level: very high
Sunny- slight ripple.  Water level: very low.
Public perception "1" except for weather. overcast- choppy water.  Lake level: very high
Clear skies- slight ripple.  Lake level: very high
Slight greenish tint. unable to take secchi disc reading due to cloudy rainy weather-clear skies-moderate wave action.
Patchy clouds- moderate wave action- pair of loons on the lake.
Pair of loons on lake- sighted 3 otters.
Windy- high wave action- sunny- clear- pair of loons on lake.  Lake level: very high
Somewhat cloudy- very wavy.  Lake level: very high
Slight cloud cover- moderate wave action.  Pair of resident loons with two chicks in bay.
Muck along shoreline- water level lowest ever in past 30 years.
Pollen on surface of lake near shoreline.
Sunny- strong west wind- and choppy lake surface.
Partly cloudy- calm water with slight ripple.  Pair of loon chicks observed.
Green film on water on north shore
Air temp 72. H2O 62. WSW wind 10-13. nesting loon- one foraging.
Air 72. H20 67. Wind light NW. Two adult loons with one chick. One eagle- one blue heron.
Air 74. H2O 73. Light east wind. One heron- one muskrat- single loon with one chick.
Wind WNW@ 10. H2O 74. One loon with chick greater than
Air 70. H2O 72. Wind SW 20 mph. Air 70. H2O 72. Wind SW 20 mph.
Wind South 15. Partly cloudy. H2O 64. Blue heron- one loon with chick.
water is 8-12 inches high due to beaver
Lake ice out on 5/12/13. Lake turned over on 5/20/13.  Observed otter and loon on nest.
4 adult eagles on the lake; 2 adult loons on the lake
Loon platform with one abandoned egg; adult loon incubating on nearby tiny- natural grassy island.
1 adult and two baby loons on lake
Two adult and two baby loons on lake
Two adult and two baby loons on lake
Two adult and two baby loons on lake.
Two adult and two baby loons on lake
1 immature loon; 2 pied-billed grebes; 4 wood ducks; 4 mallards; 1 ring-billed gull; and one muskrat on lake
1 adult and 1 loon chick near platform
observed 2 adult and one loon chick plus 3 adult bald eagles
1 adult and one loon chick and one Great blue heron observed
2 adult and one loon chick plus 1 adult eagle plus one osprey observed
1 adult and one looln chick plus one adult eagle observed
1 loon chick and no adult loons observed
2 adult loons in 1/2 hour battle- one chasing the other; 1 adult bald eagle 2 adult loons in 1/2 hour battle- one chasing the other; 1 adult bald eagle
Large quantities of uprooted wild celery floating in the lake; a major die off.
2 adult loons; still large quantities of wild celery floating in the lake; algae bloom in the water column
2 adult loons; algae bloom in the water column; still lots of floating- uprooted wild celery
2 adult loons; one adult eagle; now massive amounts of wild celery floating all around the shoreline
1 adult eagle; 1 adult loon; 1 osprey; 2 Great blue herons; 12 mallards
1 adult eagle; 1 osprey; 1 loon; algae in the water column
1 adult and 1 immature bald eagle; 1 otter
2 adult but no loon chicks; loon chicks disappeared.
2 adult loons but no chicks 2 adult loons but no chicks
1 adult eagle- 1 immature eagle- 1 adult loon
Moderate wind; 2 adult loons and 1 chick
2 adult and 1 loon chick- 1 adult eagle- 1 muskrat
Some northern water milfoil floating on the surface

2 otters; 1 adult eagle;  1 adult and 1 loon chick; more northern water milfoil uprooted and floating on the surface  2 otters; 1 adult eagle;  1 adult and 1 loon chick; more northern water milfoil uprooted and floating on the surface
2 adult and 1 loon chick; 2 adult and 3 immature trumpeter swans; now large masses of northern water milfoil floating on the surface
2 adult eagles; 6 common mergansers; 1 loon; 2 gulls; beaver cutting some alder in north bay 2 adult eagles; 6 common mergansers; 1 loon; 2 gulls; beaver cutting some alder in north bay
A little windy. Beaver dam out - lake low. Spring was late.
2 adult and 1 loon chick; 1 hen mallard and 2 chicks; 1 gull- 1 adult bald eagle
